## Best Practices

- Use clean and correctly labeled data.
- Split data into training and testing datasets.
- Start with simple models before advanced ones.
- Evaluate model performance using appropriate metrics.
- Avoid overfitting by testing with unseen data.

---

## Summary

Supervised Learning is a Machine Learning technique where models learn from labeled data to make predictions. It is commonly used for classification and regression problems and powers many real-world applications such as spam detection, fraud detection, and price prediction.
